.SH NAME
SpeechRecognition.soundstart_event \- SpeechRecognition: soundstart
event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]soundstart\f[B]\f[R] event of the Web Speech API is fired
when any sound \[em] recognizable speech or not \[em] has been detected.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
